6 An Act relating to notaries public; amending 49 O.S.
2021, Sections 1 and 2, which relate to appointment
7 and oath, signature, bond, and seal; requiring
certain national criminal history record check;
8 increasing certain fees and bond requirements for
commission; updating statutory language; and
9 providing an effective date.
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 49 O.S. 2021, Section 1, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 1. The Secretary of State shall appoint and commission
15 in this state notaries public, who shall hold their office for four
16 (4) years. An applicant for a notary commission shall be eighteen
17 (18) years of age or older, a citizen of the United States, and
18 employed within this state or a legal resident of this state. A
19 national criminal history record check, as defined in Section 150.9
20 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes, shall be conducted
21 electronically of any applicant for a notary commission, including
22 any applicant for renewal. The Oklahoma State Bureau of
23 Investigation (OSBI) shall electronically obtain fingerprints of the
24 applicant and require that the person pay a search fee not to exceed
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1028 Page 1

1 Fift y Dollars ($50.00) or the cost of the search, whichever is the
2 lesser amount. The fees shall be deposited in the OSBI Revolving
3 Fund. The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation shall provide the
4 national criminal history record check to the Secretary of State
5 within fourteen (14) working days from the receipt of the request.
6 OSBI may contact the Federal Bureau of Investigation to obtain the
7 information requested. A felony conviction shall be grounds for
8 removal of a person from the office of notary public and shall
9 preclude a person from further applying for or renewing a notary
10 commission. All notary commissions shall run in the name and by the
11 authority of the State of Oklahoma, be signed by the Secretary of
12 State, and sealed with the Great Seal of the State of Oklahoma.
13 Commissions shall not be attested. Any person filing an application
14 for a new notary commission shall pay Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00)
15 Fifty Dollars ($50.00) to the Secretary of State with the
16 application. Any person filing an application for a renewal of a
17 notary commission shall pay Twenty Dollars ($20.00) Forty-five
18 Dollars ($45.00) to the Secretary of State with the application.
19 Any person requiring “same day filing service” shall pay Twenty-five
20 Dollars ($25.00) Fifty Dollars ($50.00) to the Secretary of State in
21 addition to the applicable filing fee. These funds shall be
22 deposited in the Revolving Fund revolving fund created for the
23 Secretary of State pursuant to the provisions of Section 276.1 of
24 Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
