1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 49 O.S. 2021, Section 2, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 2. A. Before entering upon the duties of his or her
4 office and not more than sixty (60) days after issuance of a notary
5 commission, every notary public so appointed and commissioned shall
6 file in the office of the Secretary of State, the notary’s oath of
7 office, the notary’s loyalty oath, the notary’s official signature,
8 an impression of the notary’s official seal, and a good and
9 sufficient bond to the State of Oklahoma, in the sum of One Thousand
10 Dollars ($1,000.00) Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00), to be
11 approved by the Secretary of State, conditioned for the faithful
12 performance of the duties of the notary’s office.
13 B. The bond required by subsection A of this section shall be
14 signed by:
15 1. An insurance agent licensed by the State of Oklahoma;
16 2. An attorney-in-fact on behalf of an insurance company with a
17 power of attorney attached; or
18 3. One or more individual sureties who are property owners in
19 the county of residence of the notary, or if a nonresident, the
20 county of employment of the notary.
21 C. The bond required by subsection A of this section shall be
22 issued for a term that commences on the bond’s effective date and
23 terminates on the commission’s expiration date. Upon the filing of
24 his or her bond with the Secretary of State, every notary public
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1028 Page 3

1 shal l pay to the Secretary of State the sum of Ten Dollars ($10.00)
2 Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) to be deposited to the credit of the
3 Revolving Fund for the Office of the Secretary of State.
4 D. A notary public shall not perform any notarial act until his
5 or her bond, official seal, oath of office and loyalty oath, as
6 required by subsection A of this section, has have been received and
7 approved by the Secretary of State.
8 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective January 1, 2026.
